After having given this more time, I'm far less enamoured with it than the 
original reigns. It isn't a bad game by any means, it just isn't as 
compelling. Overall, the writing is very... clumsy to, put it kindly; In 
some places it even feels like a lazy translation from another language. 
The game does no favours for either feminism or paganism, opting instead to 
reduce them to a bad joke in the name of satire. I would accept this were 
it not for the incredibly ham-fisted ways in which these topics were 
handled. It tries to be funny but it fails dismally, so the end result just 
feels petty. The gameplay mechanics have become needlessly convoluted and 
dull, it's no longer a game one can simply pick up and play for ten 
minutes, like one could with the original Reigns, as there are too many 
variables to keep track of. It's a bit of a bloated mess which leaves the 
queen feeling far less powerful than the king of the original game. I fully 
understand that may be the point, but considering this is a fantasy setting 
-- not a historical one -- it feels disingenuous to make that claim. In a 
fantasy reality you don't need a massive division between genders. And if 
the point is to have a meaningful message then wouldn't it be more 
constructive to make the topic of that message not a bad joke? Considering 
the jokey handling of feminism, the impotence of the queen doesn't say good 
things. And then there's the overall lack of creativity. The scientist just 
being gender-swapped, for example, but otherwise serving exactly the same 
purpose. The cards and scenarios are less fun in general; The original had 
a House of Lycanthropic Ill-Repute! This has nothing nearly so 
entertaining. Here's the thing: It's an okay game but the original is a far 
superior one. Funnier, more heartfelt, better made, more creative, and less 
convoluted and bloated. By comparison this is dull, uninspired, and worse 
off for it. If you've never played Reigns? I recommend the original, 
wholeheartedly. If you have, and you're looking for more? Skip this, it'll 
only lead to disappointment.

There is no player initiative or power. You're left helpless with no advisor. It's just dumb, imo, really not for me but I see a ton of other people like it so maybe I'm missing the point. I'd still like a refund, and since there seems to be no button here to request one, here I am.

Solid successor to an excellent first game. It still maintains the charm & humour of the original while still forging it's own path. The items add a new level of intricacy & your ability to keep balance has definitely been made a lot more difficult. My only complaints are that   a few times it's seemed like I've been taken to an ending even when the corresponding attribute's meter hasn't quite filled up. On top of that it does feel far too simple to have the people's attribute overflow, leading to you repeatedly running into the same ending. I suppose it could be by design but it's the only one I've repeatedly struggled with. Overall I'd also say the sheer level of variety in story or endings is also a little lacking compared to the first. Still, it's a fun game & great way to kill some time, though I'd recommend starting with the first if you haven't played it yet.

I played the original and was super excited to play this iteration - one of the few mobile games I've ever been willing to pay for, let alone at full price (both times) and they're well worth it. No ads or in-app purchases to speak of and the game play is both dark and funny - while at the same time, engaging despite some of the repetitive aspects, which is important to the game play because you need to remember to do things different than the last time you did (when it doesn't work out). The only issue is the lack of more direct information about what to do with certain items (besides a barely helpful hint in the glowing arrow button) and using the wrong item at the wrong time results in rather fiendish punishment to your stats across the board so you kind of have to get it right the first time and who knows what to do when you do. It'd be nice to have a little more feedback on what choices to make - I've considered consulting a walk-through, it's that dense. And after reading a walk-through for the first game way back when, I wouldn't be surprised if it's just as complicated and impossibly dense as the first one was (at least to "beat" the game). At any rate, it's worth paying for and playing through just to enjoy yourself without ever even hoping to "beat" the game, that's how great it is - and that's saying something.

I loved the first Reigns, and still do! It's an amazing game, and I literally played it every day for at least a month, and still played it now and again after that, and loved every second of it, and this game, more than lives up to its predecessor!  I have not played too much of it yet, but I have discovered about 300 cards, and that's about a fourth of all the cards currently in the game, and it is so much better than the first one! It is already my favourite mobile game ever, right above the first.  This game introduces some new mechanics, like a few items that you unlock, that you can use to interact with a few different cards, and use to kind of solve little puzzles with who to show them to etc. And they can be used to unlock the bigger plot points and other fun stuff.  But don't worry. The core gameplay is still the same, just with all new cards, characters, and plot that is so much better than the first. The items are used pretty rarely.  The fact that you now play as the queen, makes everything a lot more interesting as well, and the cards and  everything is much better written than the first one too, and the game is huge, and you get even more than what you pay for! I would be okay with paying a lot more for this game, but the fact that it has such a low price tag, makes it a must by.
